hpnicfVsi.name: hpnicfVsi
hpnicfVsi.description: The MIB for VSI (Virtual Switch Instance).

hpnicfVsiNextAvailableVsiIndex.name: hpnicfVsiNextAvailableVsiIndex
hpnicfVsiNextAvailableVsiIndex.description: Next available VSI entry index for creating VSI. Its value ranges from 0x1 to 0xFFFFFFFF. The invalid value 0xFFFFFFFF indicates that no VSI entry can be created.

hpnicfVsiTable.name: hpnicfVsiTable
hpnicfVsiTable.description: A table for configuring VSI parameters.

hpnicfVsiEntry.name: hpnicfVsiEntry
hpnicfVsiEntry.description: An entry for configuring VSI parameters.

hpnicfVsiIndex.name: hpnicfVsiIndex
hpnicfVsiIndex.description: Index of VSI. Its value ranges from 0x1 to 0xFFFFFFFE.

hpnicfVsiName.name: hpnicfVsiName
hpnicfVsiName.description: Name of VSI. Max string length of VSI name is 31.

hpnicfVsiMode.name: hpnicfVsiMode
hpnicfVsiMode.description: Mode of VSI. Martini mode indicated this VSI supports VPLS service signalled using LDP. Kompella indicated this VSI supports VPLS service signalled using BGP. Minm indicated this VSI supports MAC-in-MAC service. Default indicated this VSI supports all services.

hpnicfMinmIsid.name: hpnicfMinmIsid
hpnicfMinmIsid.description: The PBB I-SID of VSI in minm or martiniAndMinm mode. It must be different for every VSI. Its value ranges from 0x1 to 0xFFFFFF. In other VSI modes, its value is invalid value 0x0.

hpnicfVsiId.name: hpnicfVsiId
hpnicfVsiId.description: Identifier of VSI in martini or martiniAndMinm mode, by default, it's the PW ID of this VSI. Its value ranges from 1 to 4294967295. In other VSI modes, its value is invalid value 0.

hpnicfVsiEnableHubSpoke.name: hpnicfVsiEnableHubSpoke
hpnicfVsiEnableHubSpoke.description: Config HubSpoke property of this VSI.

hpnicfVsiAdminState.name: hpnicfVsiAdminState
hpnicfVsiAdminState.description: Set VSI admin state as adminUp or adminDown.

hpnicfVsiRowStatus.name: hpnicfVsiRowStatus
hpnicfVsiRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.

hpnicfVsiSpbIsid.name: hpnicfVsiSpbIsid
hpnicfVsiSpbIsid.description: The SPB I-SID of VSI in minm or martiniAndMinm mode. It must be different for every VSI. Its value ranges from 0xFF to 0xFFFFFF. In other VSI modes, its value is invalid value 0x0.

hpnicfVsiVxlanID.name: hpnicfVsiVxlanID
hpnicfVsiVxlanID.description: VXLAN ID, in the range of 0x0 to 0xFFFFFF. Value 0xFFFFFFFF means this VSI does not enable VXLAN service.

hpnicfVsiFlooding.name: hpnicfVsiFlooding
hpnicfVsiFlooding.description: The capability of MAC(Media Access Control) flooding.

hpnicfVsiLocalMacCount.name: hpnicfVsiLocalMacCount
hpnicfVsiLocalMacCount.description: The number of VSI local MAC addresses.

hpnicfVsiXconnectTable.name: hpnicfVsiXconnectTable
hpnicfVsiXconnectTable.description: A table for configuring xconnect parameters.

hpnicfVsiXconnectEntry.name: hpnicfVsiXconnectEntry
hpnicfVsiXconnectEntry.description: An entry for configuring xconnect parameters. Each entry means connecting a service instance of a interface to a VSI.

hpnicfVsiXconnectIfIndex.name: hpnicfVsiXconnectIfIndex
hpnicfVsiXconnectIfIndex.description: Index of the interface associated with the VSI.

hpnicfVsiXconnectEvcSrvInstId.name: hpnicfVsiXconnectEvcSrvInstId
hpnicfVsiXconnectEvcSrvInstId.description: Index of the service instance associated with the VSI.

hpnicfVsiXconnectVsiName.name: hpnicfVsiXconnectVsiName
hpnicfVsiXconnectVsiName.description: Name of VSI. Max string length of VSI name is 31.

hpnicfVsiXconnectAccessMode.name: hpnicfVsiXconnectAccessMode
hpnicfVsiXconnectAccessMode.description: Access mode of this service instance.

hpnicfVsiXconnectHubSpoke.name: hpnicfVsiXconnectHubSpoke
hpnicfVsiXconnectHubSpoke.description: Config HubSpoke property of this service instance.

hpnicfVsiXconnectRowStatus.name: hpnicfVsiXconnectRowStatus
hpnicfVsiXconnectRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.

hpnicfVsiPwBindTable.name: hpnicfVsiPwBindTable
hpnicfVsiPwBindTable.description: A table for PW(PseudoWire) mapping to VSI.

hpnicfVsiPwBindEntry.name: hpnicfVsiPwBindEntry
hpnicfVsiPwBindEntry.description: Each entry means a PW mapping to a VSI.

hpnicfVsiPwIndex.name: hpnicfVsiPwIndex
hpnicfVsiPwIndex.description: A unique index for the conceptual row identifying a PW in the pwTable.

hpnicfVsiPwBindAttributes.name: hpnicfVsiPwBindAttributes
hpnicfVsiPwBindAttributes.description: This bit mask indicates optional values for this PW. The following describes these bit fields: noSplitHorizon flag indicates that the PW disable split horizon forwarding. hub flag indicates that the PW as the hub link the VSI.

hpnicfVsiPwBindRowStatus.name: hpnicfVsiPwBindRowStatus
hpnicfVsiPwBindRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry. A row entry cannot be modified when the value of this object is 'active'.

hpnicfVsiFloodMacTable.name: hpnicfVsiFloodMacTable
hpnicfVsiFloodMacTable.description: A table of MAC addresses enabled with selective flooding.

hpnicfVsiFloodMacEntry.name: hpnicfVsiFloodMacEntry
hpnicfVsiFloodMacEntry.description: Each entry represents a selective flooding MAC.

hpnicfVsiFloodMacRowStatus.name: hpnicfVsiFloodMacRowStatus
hpnicfVsiFloodMacRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry.

hpnicfVsiLocalMacTable.name: hpnicfVsiLocalMacTable
hpnicfVsiLocalMacTable.description: A table for VSI local MAC addresses.

hpnicfVsiLocalMacEntry.name: hpnicfVsiLocalMacEntry
hpnicfVsiLocalMacEntry.description: A local MAC address of VSI.

hpnicfVsiLocalMacIfIndex.name: hpnicfVsiLocalMacIfIndex
hpnicfVsiLocalMacIfIndex.description: Index of the interface associated with the MAC address.

hpnicfVsiLocalMacSrvID.name: hpnicfVsiLocalMacSrvID
hpnicfVsiLocalMacSrvID.description: Index of the service instance associated with the MAC address.
